The paper focuses on characterizing and analyzing big data workloads from a micro-architectural perspective, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The workloads are related to big data processing, which involves managing and analyzing large datasets, and thus can also be categorized under databases (cs.DB) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the software stacks used in big data processing and their impact on performance, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the workload characterization on system design, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
